{
  "stem": "4753.9",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Or I found it [INAUDIBLE] in that place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When we arrived to the ghetto and brought in many things-- what we thought we will be able to use wherever we go, like toothpaste, where we put in money.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Many people brought in books.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The German SS ordered us young people to go there and collect everything and put it in a certain room, carrying every so-called merchandise, whatever the Jews brought in for their own use.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And between all of the wonderful things what I saw there, I just rescued-- stole a book, because, for me, I loved to read.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's-- I wanted to read that book.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that was Sinclair's or something like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, and that was another book what really shook me up, also an American book.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the Hungarian title what I remember the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, like a wild animal who was chased, and the Hungarian translated-- translation that was the title of the book, And I wanted to read that, and I started to read that in the ghetto and in the-- the bricks factory.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was, for me, the most important value then.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was always very idealistic.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I always believed in goodness and beauty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't know how I could look for beauty in books in that certain situation where we were.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The barracks were-- when we arrived to Auschwitz and, finally, we came to our barracks-- they were wooden barracks.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had windows but no glass panel in it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the whole place was just an empty-- excuse me-- empty open territory with a lot of wooden barracks and three sides that was fenced around with electrified wire, one side that wasn't.",
      "word_count": 33
    }
  ],
